    "causal_summary": "cli-external-orchestration is the single public advisor identity for four CLI dispatch orchestrators, folded into one parent hub. cli-opencode enables external AI runtimes and in-OpenCode operators to invoke opencode run for full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime dispatch, plus parallel detached sessions for ablation, worker farms, and cross-AI handback, defaulting to the direct deepseek provider. cli-claude-code enables external AI assistants to invoke Anthropic's Claude Code CLI for deep reasoning, surgical code editing, structured JSON-schema output, code review, and agent delegation. cli-codex enables OpenAI-backed coding, repo analysis, PR review, web research, and cross-model validation through the Codex CLI, and fails closed when codex is absent. cli-cursor enables Cursor CLI (cursor-agent) dispatch for sandboxed coding, Composer-model-specific opinions, and read-only plan/ask exploration; it fails closed when cursor-agent is absent and shares its entire config surface (hooks, MCP, rules) with the Cursor editor, unlike every sibling's tool-private config directory. It matters because it gives all four dispatch paths one coherent advisor identity while each mode keeps its own dispatch contract, hard rules, and self-invocation guard; the executor-delegation scorer sources its executor alias table from this hub's mode-registry.json rather than a top-level family filter, so delegation prompts keep resolving to the correct executor-kind string.",
